1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 905 of Title 40, unless there is
3 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. Pursuant to the provisions of Section 904 of Title 40 of the
5 Oklahoma Statutes, the Oklahoma Workforce Commission shall implement
6 programs in this state to address the following:
7 1. Development of a workforce in high demand occupations or
8 critical occupations as determined by the Oklahoma Workforce
9 Commission. Actions taken by the Commission may include:
10 a. identifying the needs of higher education institutions
11 suited for certain high demand or critical workforce
12 areas and helping the institutions develop and
13 implement plans to address those needs,
14 b. identify outcomes based on funding,
15 c. identifying and partnering for scholarship match
16 opportunities for students interested in these high
17 demand and critical workforce fields, and
18 d. helping institutions increase program capacity;
19 2. Development of work-based learning opportunities, which may
20 include, but not be limited to, internships, apprenticeships, and
21 other career exploration and exposure; and
22 3. Development of innovation within public schools as defined
23 in Section 1-106 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes that supports
24 workforce success, which may include:
Req. No. 13635 Page 5

1 a. developing enhanced or unique education pathways,
2 b. utilizing development grants for basic skills
3 development,
4 c. utilizing regulatory innovation grants, and
5 d. assisting in the development of career-connected high
6 schools.
7 B. The Commission may administer these programs through funds
8 in the Oklahoma Workforce Commission Revolving Fund created in
9 Section 3 of this act.
10 C. The Commission shall promulgate rules necessary to implement
11 the provisions of this section.
12 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 906 of Title 40, unless there is
14 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
16 fund for the Oklahoma Workforce Commission to be designated the
17 "Oklahoma Workforce Commission Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a
18 continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall
19 consist of all monies received by the Commission from
20 appropriations, donations, grants, and other sources of funding.
21 All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby
22 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Commission for
23 the purpose of duties imposed upon the Commission by law.
24 Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon warrants issued by
Req. No. 13635 Page 6

1 the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by law with
2 the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services for
3 approval and payment.
4 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
